-- Jeronimo Martins to Start Operations in Colombia’s Eje Cafetero
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-12-13T08:47:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-13/jeronimo-martins-to-start-operations-in-colombia-s-eje-cafetero.html
Jeronimo Martins SGPS SA (JMT) ,  Portugal ’s
biggest retailer, said it will start operations in Colombia in
that country’s coffee-producing Eje Cafetero region, a company
spokeswoman said.  “Our operation will start in Eje Cafetero,” Rita Fragoso
said in a phone interview yesterday.  Jeronimo Martins, owner of the Pingo Doce supermarket chain
in Portugal and Poland’s leading discount-store operator,
Biedronka, reiterated on Dec. 11 a plan to open 30 to 40 stores
in Colombia next year and invest 400 million euros in the
Southern American country through 2015.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
